.TH "do_truncation" 9 "do_truncation" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
do_truncation \- truncate an inode.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" do_truncation
.BI "(struct ubifs_info *c "  ","
.BI "struct inode *inode "  ","
.BI "const struct iattr *attr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "c" 12
UBIFS file-system description object
.IP "inode" 12
inode to truncate
.IP "attr" 12
inode attribute changes description
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function implements VFS '->\fBsetattr\fP' call when the inode is truncated
to a smaller size. Returns zero in case of success and a negative error code
in case of failure.
